    <div class="about__text">
      <p class="about__lead">I'm Pia Schelli — a UX designer with a background in business administration. That combination shapes everything about how I work.</p>

      <p>Most design problems aren't really design problems. They're organisational decisions, resource constraints, or unclear strategy surfacing as UX symptoms. I'm trained to read both layers — the user's experience and the business context underneath it — which means I can frame problems that actually get solved.</p>

      <p>I specialise in early-stage product work: research, concept development, facilitation, and iterative prototyping. I'm most useful when the brief is still ambiguous and the path forward isn't obvious.</p>

      <p>Currently based in Germany, open to projects in German and English.</p>
    </div>

